 y teams of 3-4 (typically a technologist/developer\, a democracy or policy
  expert\, and a designer or UX innovator)\; residents of the 46 Council of
  Europe member states\; coding experience is not required for every team m
 ember. FORMAT: four online warm-up sessions\, then a three-day in-person f
 inale at the Palais de l'Europe\, Strasbourg\, 17-19 June 2026.\n\nOrganis
 ation: Council of Europe (under the Monaco Presidency of the Committee of 
 Ministers)\, in partnership with No Hate Speech Week and Microsoft\nLocati
 on: Palais de l'Europe\, Strasbourg\, France (hybrid: four online warm-up 
 sessions leading to a three-day in-person finale)\nAward: EUR 50\,000 Micr
 osoft-funded prize pool distributed among winning teams. Travel and accomm
 odation covered for the 20 selected finalist teams. No application fee.\nD
 uration: Online warm-up sessions plus three-day in-person hackathon (17-19
  June 2026)\n\nMore: https://democracyhackathon.coe.int/?utm_source=artifi
 cialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://democracyhackathon.coe.int/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantde
 sk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Palais de l'Europe\, Strasbourg\, France (hybrid: four online warm
 -up sessions leading to a three-day in-person finale)
