DESCRIPTION:The AGI Governance Fellowship is the inaugural three-week inten
 sive run by Johns Hopkins University's School of Government and Policy (SO
 GP) to develop the next generation of leaders in AI governance. COVERS: fr
 ontier AI legislation at state and federal levels\; building societal resi
 lience amid rapid capability growth\; democratic practices in AGI alignmen
 t\; and designing new governing institutions for the AGI era. WHO SHOULD A
 PPLY: early-career researchers and practitioners (within roughly eight yea
 rs of undergrad) with solid foundations in AI governance\, including congr
 essional staffers\, AGI company employees\, recent CS or policy PhDs\, and
  nonprofit/civil society professionals\; a postgraduate degree or equivale
 nt experience is required. This is a capstone program for rising leaders\,
  not an intro course. FUNDING: travel\, accommodation\, and meals are full
 y covered. DATES: 8-25 September 2026 at the Hopkins Bloomberg Center in W
 ashington\, D.C. (in-person only). DEADLINE: apply by 15 July 2026 for ful
 l consideration\; rolling applications accepted. APPLY: https://sogp.jh.ed
 u/agi-governance-fellowship/\n\nOrganisation: Johns Hopkins University\, S
 chool of Government and Policy (SOGP)\nLocation: Hopkins Bloomberg Center\
 , Washington\, D.C. (in-person only)\nAward: Fully funded: travel\, accomm
 odation\, and meals covered.\nDuration: Three-week in-person intensive\, 8
 -25 September 2026\n\nMore: https://sogp.jh.edu/agi-governance-fellowship/
 ?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
